-- Basu Says Major India Reforms Unlikely Before 2014, PTI Reports
-- B y   T u s h a r   D h a r a
-- 2012-04-20T05:17:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-20/basu-says-major-india-reforms-unlikely-before-2014-pti-reports.html
Major economic reforms in  India  are
unlikely to take place before 2014, when a new federal
government is voted into power, Kaushik Basu, chief economic
adviser in the finance ministry, said in Washington yesterday,
Press Trust of India reported.  Basu, who said India will be one of the fastest-growing
economies after 2015, identified the opening up of the retail
sector as one of the key future reforms, according to the
report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tushar Dhara in New Delhi at 
 tdhara1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephanie Phang at 
 sphang@bloomberg.net . 